<paragraph id="2D553688FFB0FFBAFF24578A808BFEA8" blockId="5.[151,1436,1992,2017]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,320]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="259" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">
<materialsCitation id="9D823CD5FFB0FFBAFF24578A808BFEA8" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1585880146" country="Canada" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="259" location="Western Hemisphere" pageId="5" pageNumber="258" specimenCount="1">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="EAEA4D0BFFB0FFB9FEA5578B8169F809" authority="Bates, 1863" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1863" box="[278,533,1992,2017]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lepturges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1F9EEA9AFFB0FFB9FEA5578B82F9F808" box="[278,389,1993,2016]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">Lepturges</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="497B4B79FFB0FFB9FE3D578B8169F809" author="Bates" box="[398,533,1992,2017]" pageId="5" pageNumber="258" refString="Bates, H. W. (1863) Contributions to an insect fauna of the Amazon Valley. Coleoptera: Longicornes. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, (3) 12, 367 - 381." type="journal article" year="1863">Bates, 1863</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in the 
<location id="28356053FFB0FFB9FCB5578B808DF809" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:A543879EFFB0FFBAFF24577C808BFEA8:28356053FFB0FFB9FCB5578B808DF809" box="[774,1009,1992,2017]" country="Canada" name="Western Hemisphere" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">Western Hemisphere</location>
from 
<collectingCountry id="55FD7618FFB0FFB9FB88578A87F3F809" box="[1083,1167,1992,2017]" name="Canada" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">Canada</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="55FD7618FFB0FFB9FB04578A8655F809" box="[1207,1321,1992,2017]" name="Argentina" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, currently divided in two subgenera: 
<emphasis id="1F9EEA9AFFB3FFBAFE7450DB819CFF47" box="[455,736,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">
<taxonomicName id="EAEA4D0BFFB3FFBAFE7450DB814AFF58" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1863" box="[455,566,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lepturges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lepturges</taxonomicName>
(sensu stricto)
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="497B4B79FFB3FFBAFD5B50DA8012FF58" author="Bates" box="[744,878,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" refString="Bates, H. W. (1863) Contributions to an insect fauna of the Amazon Valley. Coleoptera: Longicornes. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, (3) 12, 367 - 381." type="journal article" year="1863">Bates, 1863</bibRefCitation>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EAEA4D0BFFB3FFBAFC1B50DB861FFF58" authority="Gilmour, 1959" authorityName="Gilmour" authorityYear="1959" box="[936,1379,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lepturges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Chaeturges">
<emphasis id="1F9EEA9AFFB3FFBAFC1B50DB87CEFF58" box="[936,1202,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Lepturges (Chaeturges)</emphasis>
Gilmour, 1959
</taxonomicName>
. The differences between these two subgenera are the presence in the last one of bristles in the lateral sides of the elytra. There are 74 species described in 
<emphasis id="1F9EEA9AFFB3FFBAFDA850A38048FF1F" box="[539,820,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">
<taxonomicName id="EAEA4D0BFFB3FFBAFDA850A381F6FF10" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1863" box="[539,650,225,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lepturges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lepturges</taxonomicName>
(sensu stricto)
</emphasis>
and 
<quantity id="EA129B6DFFB3FFBAFCDE50A280DBFF10" box="[877,935,223,248]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" unit="in" value="20.0">20 in</quantity>
<emphasis id="1F9EEA9AFFB3FFBAFC0350A387BEFF10" box="[944,1218,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">
<taxonomicName id="EAEA4D0BFFB3FFBAFC0350A387C2FF10" authority="(Chaeturges)" authorityName="Chaeturges" box="[944,1214,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lepturges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lepturges (Chaeturges)</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
After 
<bibRefCitation id="497B4B79FFB3FFBAFABF50A286E4FF10" author="Bates" box="[1292,1432,223,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" refString="Bates, H. W. (1863) Contributions to an insect fauna of the Amazon Valley. Coleoptera: Longicornes. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, (3) 12, 367 - 381." type="journal article" year="1863">Bates (1863</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="497B4B79FFB3FFBAFF24514683AEFEF4" author="Bates" box="[151,210,260,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" refString="Bates, H. W. (1872) On the longicorn Coleoptera of Chontales, Nicaragua. The Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 1872, 163 - 238. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1872. tb 01888. x" type="journal article" year="1872">1872</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="497B4B79FFB3FFBAFF6E5146826BFEF4" author="Bates" box="[221,279,260,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" refString="Bates, H. W. (1881) Biologia Centrali - Americana, Insecta, Coleoptera. London, 5, pp. 153 - 224." type="journal article" year="1881">1881</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="497B4B79FFB3FFBAFE9051468220FEF5" author="Bates" box="[291,348,260,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" refString="Bates, H. W. (1885) Biologia Centrali - Americana, Insecta, Coleoptera, suppl. to Longicornia. London, 5, pp. 249 - 436." type="journal article" year="1885">1885</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="497B4B79FFB3FFBAFE2851468149FEF4" author="Melzer" box="[411,565,260,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" refString="Melzer, J. (1928) Longicorneos do Brasil, novos ou pouco conhecidos (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Archivos do Instituto Biologico, 1, 143 - 158." type="journal article" year="1928">Melzer (1928</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="497B4B79FFB3FFBAFDF251468100FEF4" author="Melzer" box="[577,636,260,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" refString="Melzer, J. (1930) Longicorneos do Brasil, novos ou pouco conhecidos II (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Archivos do Instituto Biologico, 3, 187 - 208." type="journal article" year="1930">1930</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="497B4B79FFB3FFBAFD34514681BFFEF4" author="Melzer" box="[647,707,260,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" refString="Melzer, J. (1934) Longicorneos americanos, principalmente do Brasil, novos ou pouco conhecidos. Arquivos do Instituto Biologico, 5, 213 - 244." type="journal article" year="1934">1934</bibRefCitation>
), Gilmour described several species (1959a, 1959b, 1961, 1962), later 
<bibRefCitation id="497B4B79FFB3FFBAFF63516A8216FEA8" author="Monne" box="[208,362,295,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" refString="Monne, M. A. (1976) O genero Lepturges (s. str.) Bates, 1863 no Leste e Sul do Brasil (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae, Acanthocinini). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 36 (2), 357 - 376." type="journal article" year="1976">Monné (1976</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="497B4B79FFB3FFBAFEC6516A82D2FEA8" author="Monne" box="[373,430,296,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" refString="Monne, M. A. (1978) O genero Lepturges (s. str.) Bates, 1863, no Norte e Centro - Oeste do Brasil (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae, Acanthocinini). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 38 (1), 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1978">1978</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="497B4B79FFB3FFBAFE5E516A805BFEA8" author="Monne" box="[493,807,295,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" refString="Tavakilian, G. L. &amp; Monne, M. A. (1989) Trois especes neotropicales nouvelles de Lepturges (Chaeturges) Gilmour, 1959 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae, Acanthocinini). L'Entomologiste, 45 (4 - 5), 273 - 282." type="journal article" year="1989">Monné &amp; Tavakilian (1989)</bibRefCitation>
add other species.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
